WESLEY CHAPEL — Another professional hockey league has found its way to Tampa Bay. The Premier Hockey Federation is hosting its annual playoffs at AdventHealth Center Ice today, Sunday and Monday. Six teams will compete for the league’s championship trophy, the Isobel Cup. The Federation — established in 2015, and formerly known as the National Women’s Hockey League — will expand to a seventh team in Montreal next season with an increased salary cap ($750,000) and full healthcare benefits for players. Here are some players you should know before play opens: F Taylor Accursi, Buffalo Beauts G Elaine Chuli, Toronto Six F Jonna Curtis, Minnesota Whitecaps F Jillian Dempsey, Boston Pride D Kali Flanagan, Boston Pride F Taylor Girard, Connecticut Whale F Mikyla Grant-Mentis, Toronto Six F Autumn MacDougall, Buffalo Beauts F Kennedy Marchment, Connecticut Whale F Madison Packer, Metropolitan Riveters F Rebecca Russo, Metropolitan Riveters F Allie Thunstrom, Minnesota Whitecaps Isobel Cup AdventHealth Center Ice, Wesley Chapel Today: Buffalo Beauts (6) vs. Boston Pride (3), 4 p.m.; Minnesota Whitecaps (5) vs. Metropolitan Riveters (4), 7:30 Sunday: TBD vs. Connecticut Whale (1), 1; TBD vs. Toronto Six (2), 4:30 Monday: Final, 9 p.m. Tickets: Sold out How to watch: All games stream on ESPN+ execept Monday’s final (ESPN2) Contact Mari Faiello at mfaiello@tampabay.com. Follow @faiello_mari. • • • The Tampa Bay Times has commemorated the Lightning’s second consecutive Stanley Cup title with a new hardcover coffee table book, Striking Twice. Order now. Sign up for Lightning Strikes, a weekly newsletter from Bolts beat writer Eduardo A. Encina that brings you closer to the ice. Never miss out on the latest with the Bucs, Rays, Lightning, Florida college sports and more. Follow our Tampa Bay Times sports team on Twitter and Facebook.